Join in the largest LIVE group breathing session on Instagram on Sunday, May 3rd. Getting together from all around the world, united by the power of our breath. Can't wait to see you all X

00:00 - Amsterdam (May 3)
08:00 - Sydney (May 3)
15:00 - Los Angeles (May 2)
18:00 - New York (May 2)

Program:
5min. - Welcoming everyone
15min. - Guided breathing
5min - Hof music

#iceman #wimhof #live #breathwork #groupbreathing #instalive #guidedbreathing #wimhofmethod #justbreathe #power #breathe #livemusic

node.text:
3 rounds of Wim Hof breathing, gradually building up.

Please keep in mind;
- Don't do the breathing exercises in a swimming pool, before going underwater, beneath the shower or piloting any vehicle, without proper supervision. - Always practice in a safe environment. Sitting or lying on the ground/couch
- Do the exercises without force and gradually build up.  Best on Empty stomach.

Download the free “Wim Hof Method” in the Appstore or Google Play for more in-depth explanations and interactive breathing exercises.

Everyone's been asking what do I think about the Coronavirus, and here it is. It's a serious matter that must not be taken too lightly. But you have the power to make a change. It is important for everyone to know how significant their individual actions are especially in such a delicate time. We need to protect ourselves, our loved ones and those in more vulnerable situations. The healthiest things you can do now is to: - wash your hands frequently - avoid touching your face
- keep social distancing - avoid coming into contact with people at risk (people over 70 and/or immunocompromised)
- don't travel unless it's extremely urgent
- avoid large public gatherings
- if you've been coughing repeatedly or you're having a fever seek medical attention and follow the directions of your local health authority
- even if you don't have symptoms you probably already know it doesn't mean you don't have the virus, so it's important to follow all the other health guidelines above in order to not further spread the virus.

In 2014 Radboud University had proven that through the WHM you can upregulate your immunity, by increasing the amount of white blood cells and B-lymphocyte cells. These cells form the army in your body that fight off micro-organisms and viruses that don’t belong there. At the same time, the WHM helps a person better influence the innate immune response resulting in lowering the severity of symptoms such as fever or headache. Overall, less inflammation and disease-like symptoms.

This study showed that you can boost your immune system through the method. The Wim Hof Method therefore could prove to be a useful tool in fighting against unwanted guests in your body by speeding the development of immunity and reducing symptoms.

I suggest you start with practicing the method and get your army ready.

Stay safe everyone. Sending you all a big hug from a distance. All the love and all the power to you. X

#iceman #wimhof #coronavirus #covid19 #safetyfirst #staysafe #justbreathe #love #health #happiness #strength #wimhofmethod

node.text:
Did you know that about 40% of all bottled water is tap water?🚰💧

Yet, an estimated 90% of the plastic water bottles we buy end up in landfills, only 10% being recycled. 

It takes up to 1,000 years for every single bottle of water to decompose. Each bottle leaks harmful chemicals into our environment along the way as it decomposes.

Studies show that the toxins decomposing bottles of water leach into our environment and cause a variety of health issues.

So make sure to carefully check the label and even the cap; if it says "from a municipal source" or "from a community water system," this means it's derived from tap. 

Or even better, ditch bottled water in favour filtered water that you can fill in reusable bottles made from more sustainable materials.

node.text:
Does the Wim Hof Method improve your athletic performance? To find out, let’s do some push-ups 💪

Step ️1: Do as many push-ups as you can to set a baseline. Most of us can only do 10-20 before becoming fatigued. 

Step 2: Now do a single round of the Wim Hof Breathing exercise. After exhaling fully try the push-ups again during the retention phase, with your breath held out on the exhale. If you feel you can, keep doing the push-ups after you breathe in for the recovery breath. 

You may be surprised to learn that suddenly you can do twice, three times, or even four times as many as you did before. Share below how many push-ups you did in step 1, and then step 2 👇
